Package com.example.flexiMed.dto

Class RequestDTO

java.lang.Object
com.example.flexiMed.dto.RequestDTO
public class RequestDTO extends Object
Data Transfer Object (DTO) for representing a request for an ambulance service. This class encapsulates all the necessary information about the request such as the user making the request, ambulance details, status, and timestamps for the various stages of the request.

  • Constructor Details

    • RequestDTO

      public RequestDTO()
      Default constructor for RequestDTO. This constructor is needed for frameworks like Jackson to map request data.

    • RequestDTO

      public RequestDTO(UUID id, UUID userId, UUID ambulanceId, RequestStatus requestStatus, LocalDateTime requestTime, LocalDateTime dispatchTime, LocalDateTime arrivalTime, double latitude, double longitude, String description)
      Parameterized constructor for RequestDTO. Initializes all fields of the request object with specified values.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique identifier for the request.
      userId - The unique identifier for the user who made the request.
      ambulanceId - The unique identifier for the assigned ambulance.
      requestStatus - The current status of the request (e.g., "PENDING", "DISPATCHED").
      requestTime - The timestamp when the request was created.
      dispatchTime - The timestamp when the ambulance was dispatched.
      arrivalTime - The timestamp when the ambulance arrived at the destination.
      latitude - The latitude of the request location.
      longitude - The longitude of the request location.
      description - A description or additional details about the request.
